--------------- RC FLAG -----------------

WEBHOMER3 is a modular interface for HOMER/SIPCapture

--------------- RC FLAG -----------------

Requirements:

	- PHP 5.2+ (w/ pecl/json, php-gd) 
	- MySQL 5.1+
	- Apache2 (w/ rewrite enabled for API)
	- HOMER/SIPCAPTURE (latest git)

Setup/Upgrade:

	- update "configuration.php" with any new parameters from "configuration_example.php"
	- create homer_statistics db (statistics.sql)
        - schedule cronjob for stat collection every 5 minutes, add db auth (statistic.pl)
	- Copy webhomer3 in your webfolder and carry your existing configuration.php
	- For production, create a symlink from old webhomer/ to webhomer3/ for config continuity
	- For testing, webhomer3 can run in parallel with other/older webhomer versions

Setup/New Users:

	- create homer_users db (homer_users.sql)
	- insert all your home nodes into homer_nodes table (see HOWTO)
	- create homer_statistics db (statistics.sql)
	- schedule cronjob for stat collection every 5 minutes, add db auth (statistic.pl)
	- customize "configuration_example.php" and rename it to "configuration.php"
	- point your browser at WEBHOMER's url and login as: test@test.com/test123
	
----------------------------------------

New Features:

	- [New] Drag & Drop UI with inline elements & cookie positioning prefs
	- [New] Time & Date controls with graph/zoom selection & interaction
	- [New] Statistics (Highcharts OR Flot) with search integration (click & select) 
	- [New] Improved Admin section with user levels, settings and service overview
	- [New] Toolbox page with SIP Message & PCAP generator & Looking-Glass Widgets
	- [New] API functions for widget development and integration with other tools
	- [New] Extensible Alarm Class for notifications and alert dispatching
	- [New] Extensible Authentication Class supporting Internal, LDAP, Radius
	- [New] IE7/8/9 Support Implemented
	- [New] Custom Size for Call Flow Image

Usage Notes:

	- All searches are obeying the time/date parameters set in search page
	  (Example: Autosearch, Search, Call-Flow)

Notes:

	- UI Glitches? Clear browser cookies (top right TRASH icon) and try again


